WEBVTT

00:01.349 --> 00:02.741
- Previously,
on "God Friended Me."

00:02.785 --> 00:05.440
- Take that, old man!
- Old, who you calling old?

00:05.483 --> 00:06.832
- You, Uncle T!

00:06.876 --> 00:08.878
- I know that you think
that he looks up to me

00:08.921 --> 00:11.054
more than you, but that
is not the case, Arthur.

00:11.098 --> 00:13.056
- What did you do?
- The God account is gone!

00:13.100 --> 00:14.405
- It must have been awkward

00:14.449 --> 00:15.928
bumping into your ex
with Miles.

00:15.972 --> 00:17.930
- You free Sunday?
- Maybe.

00:17.974 --> 00:20.585
- Helping people
isn't a burden.

00:20.629 --> 00:22.457
It's an opportunity.

00:23.632 --> 00:25.155
- ♪ I testify

00:25.199 --> 00:26.765
[groovy music]

00:26.809 --> 00:28.593
- Six weeks ago,
I got a friend request

00:28.637 --> 00:30.421
from someone
calling themselves God.

00:30.465 --> 00:33.294
They started sending me
people in need of help.

00:33.337 --> 00:35.687
For the very few of you that
have stuck around to listen,

00:35.731 --> 00:38.864
you know that I have resisted.
Not anymore.

00:38.908 --> 00:41.737
I am going to see
where this road takes me.

00:41.780 --> 00:44.174
Now, that doesn't mean
I'm going to stop looking

00:44.218 --> 00:46.611
for who's behind it,
but there's a freedom

00:46.655 --> 00:48.265
in accepting this new path.

00:48.309 --> 00:50.485
A clarity for what
I'm trying to do.

00:50.528 --> 00:52.922
I am ready to
start growing my audience

00:52.965 --> 00:54.619
one listener at a time.

00:54.663 --> 00:56.360
So if you see
any of my posters,

00:56.404 --> 00:58.101
please get the word out.

00:58.145 --> 01:00.277
The Millennial Prophet
is making a comeback.

01:00.321 --> 01:02.149
♪

01:02.192 --> 01:05.456
- You know, I got to say, bro.
This poster is pretty fire.

01:05.500 --> 01:07.328
- Yeah, it's smart, Miles.

01:07.371 --> 01:09.112
I mean, grassroots marketing
will get you a new audience.

01:09.156 --> 01:10.853
- Yeah, well,
it's what I need, you know?

01:10.896 --> 01:12.333
Considering I lost
most of my listeners

01:12.376 --> 01:14.030
after I changed my message.

01:14.074 --> 01:17.251
- Well, you are the atheist
working for God now,

01:17.294 --> 01:19.209
so I kind of understand
the confusion.

01:19.253 --> 01:22.299
- Dude, there is no confusion.
We all know it is not God.

01:22.343 --> 01:26.086
- True, but whoever's doing
this already unfriended you.

01:26.129 --> 01:27.478
All right, this could have
all been over.

01:27.522 --> 01:28.871
You know, you're the one
who chose

01:28.914 --> 01:31.352
to friend that maniac back.
Why?

01:31.395 --> 01:33.354
- Because it gives me
a sense of purpose.

01:33.397 --> 01:35.138
- So you're basically working
for the God account?

01:35.182 --> 01:37.793
- I'd say it's more
like a partnership.

01:37.836 --> 01:40.404
[cell phone chimes]

01:40.448 --> 01:42.406
- What's up?
- Uh, it's Eli.

01:42.450 --> 01:43.625
He wants to get dinner.

01:45.496 --> 01:47.977
- Official date?
- Yeah, but I'm--

01:48.020 --> 01:49.065
I don't know if I'm ready
to go there again.

01:49.109 --> 01:50.458
- Why not?

01:50.501 --> 01:52.155
- I mean, we broke up
for a reason.

01:52.199 --> 01:53.983
Who's to say it doesn't end
the exact same way?

01:54.026 --> 01:55.202
- Just because
you guys have a history

01:55.245 --> 01:57.726
doesn't meant it'll repeat.

01:57.769 --> 01:59.728
- Okay, all this talk about
dinner has got me starving.

01:59.771 --> 02:01.208
- Dude, you're always starving.

02:03.471 --> 02:05.429
You know what?
- What?

02:05.473 --> 02:07.475
- Dinner's on me?
- What?

02:07.518 --> 02:10.521
- Just a little thank you
for helping me spread the word.

02:10.565 --> 02:11.957
You guys figure out
what you want,

02:12.001 --> 02:14.395
and I'll just hail us a cab.
- Okay.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.527
- Taxi, taxi!

02:16.571 --> 02:18.442
[cell phone chimes]

02:18.486 --> 02:20.270
[bright musical flourish]

02:20.314 --> 02:21.576
Look, guys, guys.

02:21.619 --> 02:23.578
I just got a new
friend suggestion.

02:23.621 --> 02:26.233
- Who is it for?
- Some guy named Hasan Amir.

02:26.276 --> 02:27.756
[horn honks]

02:27.799 --> 02:29.453
Hey, there's our cab.

02:29.497 --> 02:32.456
[tense music]

02:32.500 --> 02:37.635
♪

02:37.679 --> 02:39.376
- Where to, my friends?

02:49.256 --> 02:52.215
Have you decided where you
would like me to take you?

02:52.259 --> 02:54.652
The Lower East Side
is a big place.

02:54.696 --> 02:56.611
Can you narrow it down
a little?

02:56.654 --> 02:59.657
- Uh, no, yeah,
we haven't decided

02:59.701 --> 03:01.224
where we want to have dinner,

03:01.268 --> 03:04.314
but if you could just
give us a second, please.

03:04.358 --> 03:05.881
- Of course.
- Just pick a place,

03:05.924 --> 03:07.752
and get him talking.

03:07.796 --> 03:11.103
- Ooh, can you drop us off at
Insomnia Cookies on Orchard?

03:11.147 --> 03:13.410
- Sure.
- Cookies, really?

03:13.454 --> 03:15.238
- What--yeah,
that was the first thing

03:15.282 --> 03:17.806
that came to my mind.
Besides, you love desserts.

03:17.849 --> 03:19.460
- That is true.

03:19.503 --> 03:23.638
- So, um, how long have you
been driving a cab?

03:23.681 --> 03:26.467
- Almost 15 years,
since I moved here.

03:26.510 --> 03:29.121
- Where are you from?
- Afghanistan.

03:29.165 --> 03:31.994
I was an engineer in Kabul.

03:32.037 --> 03:34.388
We won the green card lottery,
so I moved my family here.

03:34.431 --> 03:36.390
[cell phone ringing]

03:36.433 --> 03:39.262
I'm sorry, my wife.
[chuckles]

03:39.306 --> 03:42.265
[speaking Dari]

03:50.621 --> 03:53.711
I--I'm sorry, there is
a problem with my son.

03:53.755 --> 03:55.365
I have to drop you off,

03:55.409 --> 03:57.280
but we are on the highway
and I can't pull over.

03:57.324 --> 03:59.804
- Yeah, no, don't stop for us.
Family is important.

03:59.848 --> 04:01.545
- Thank you.

04:01.589 --> 04:04.026
[tense music]

04:04.069 --> 04:06.115
[tires screech]

04:06.158 --> 04:08.552
- I'm 24 years old,
I can't live like this anymore.

04:08.596 --> 04:11.729
- Please, don't go.
At least talk to you father.

04:11.773 --> 04:13.514
- Mateen, your mother told me

04:13.557 --> 04:15.429
that you have a cell phone
hidden in your room.

04:15.472 --> 04:18.040
Who are you talking to that you
don't want us to know about?

04:18.083 --> 04:20.303
- Why do you have to know
who I call, who I talk to?

04:20.347 --> 04:22.523
You don't have to control
every aspect of my life.

04:22.566 --> 04:24.133
- I feel this guy's pain.

04:24.176 --> 04:26.875
- As long as you live
under this roof,

04:26.918 --> 04:29.704
you will listen to what
we are telling you.

04:29.747 --> 04:31.575
- Then I guess I shouldn't
be living here anymore.

04:31.619 --> 04:34.535
- Mateen!
Mateen!

04:34.578 --> 04:37.538
[dramatic music]

04:37.581 --> 04:40.889
♪

04:47.461 --> 04:51.160
- Uh, this really
isn't necessary.

04:51.203 --> 04:53.380
- Oh, you said you were
heading out for dinner.

04:53.423 --> 04:55.295
- True, but when we got
in the cab,

04:55.338 --> 04:57.471
we were just expecting the
ride, not the actual meal.

04:57.514 --> 04:59.342
- It's really good.
- After my husband

04:59.386 --> 05:00.648
drove you all the way out here,

05:00.691 --> 05:02.214
the least we can do
is feed you.

05:02.258 --> 05:03.781
- Well, thank you.

05:03.825 --> 05:06.480
Um, and really, with everything
that's going on,

05:06.523 --> 05:09.004
I hope that we're
not intruding.

05:09.047 --> 05:11.659
- Oh, things will blow over
with my son.

05:11.702 --> 05:13.617
It always does.

05:13.661 --> 05:16.794
- If you will excuse me,
I need to study.

05:16.838 --> 05:18.622
- We're having guests, Tarah.

05:18.666 --> 05:21.408
- Our guests aren't going to
help me study for the LSATs.

05:21.451 --> 05:24.585
- Tarah graduated
top of her class at Colombia.

05:24.628 --> 05:28.328
One day, she will be
a great lawyer.

05:28.371 --> 05:30.678
Go ahead, bubbah.
- It was nice meeting you.

05:33.768 --> 05:36.248
- My children have spent
more time here in America

05:36.292 --> 05:37.772
than in Afghanistan,

05:37.815 --> 05:40.601
and I'm grateful that
they have grown up here,

05:40.644 --> 05:43.168
but it's very difficult

05:43.212 --> 05:46.607
to maintain our Islamic faith
and values.

05:46.650 --> 05:50.915
My daughter, Tarah,
remains devout.

05:50.959 --> 05:54.745
But I fear my son
is slipping away.

05:54.789 --> 05:57.052
[tense music]

05:57.095 --> 05:58.967
Faith...

05:59.010 --> 06:02.187
is the most important thing
in our lives.

06:02.231 --> 06:04.842
Clearly, you feel
the same way, Miles.

06:04.886 --> 06:07.715
♪

06:07.758 --> 06:09.281
- Where'd you get that idea?

06:09.325 --> 06:11.153
- I saw the poster
you had in my cab.

06:11.196 --> 06:14.809
Um, The Millennial Prophet?

06:14.852 --> 06:18.421
Clearly, it's a podcast
about your beliefs.

06:18.465 --> 06:20.989
- Yeah, it's more of, like,
a play on words kind of thing.

06:21.032 --> 06:24.471
- What do you mean?
- I'm an atheist.

06:24.514 --> 06:27.474
[soft dramatic music]

06:27.517 --> 06:28.866
♪

06:28.910 --> 06:29.954
- [clears throat]

06:34.394 --> 06:36.352
- Thanks for the ride, Hasan.
- My pleasure.

06:36.396 --> 06:39.442
- All right.
- May I say something?

06:39.486 --> 06:40.878
- Yeah.

06:40.922 --> 06:44.752
- You are a very nice person,
Miles,

06:44.795 --> 06:49.670
and I hope you don't
take this the wrong way, but...

06:49.713 --> 06:51.236
I believe you are lost.

06:51.280 --> 06:52.890
[tense music]

06:52.934 --> 06:54.805
♪

06:54.849 --> 06:58.200
- Just because I don't believe
in God doesn't mean I'm lost,

06:58.243 --> 07:01.072
just like Mateen
wanting some independence

07:01.116 --> 07:02.987
doesn't mean
he's slipping away from you.

07:03.031 --> 07:04.728
You should talk to him,

07:04.772 --> 07:06.687
try to find some common ground.

07:06.730 --> 07:08.993
- I appreciate your concern.
- Mm-hmm.

07:09.037 --> 07:12.649
- But I have faith that my son
will return

07:12.693 --> 07:13.998
when he is ready.

07:14.042 --> 07:15.391
- See, me and my dad disagreed

07:15.435 --> 07:17.349
about that same thing
in the past.

07:17.393 --> 07:20.440
Trust me, the longer
you let this go,

07:20.483 --> 07:23.617
the harder it will be
to fix it.

07:23.660 --> 07:26.924
- It was very nice
meeting you, Miles.

07:26.968 --> 07:28.448
- You, too.

07:28.491 --> 07:30.754
- Good night.
- Good night.

07:30.798 --> 07:33.888
♪

07:33.931 --> 07:36.891
- No, no, no, no, no.
The inspector comes tomorrow,

07:36.934 --> 07:39.763
which means I need
the windows installed today.

07:39.807 --> 07:42.592
Hell, my brother-in-law
baptized your first child,

07:42.636 --> 07:44.507
which makes us
practically family.

07:44.551 --> 07:47.467
Great, thank you.

07:47.510 --> 07:49.033
[grunts]

07:49.077 --> 07:51.471
Arthur, I'm sorry.
Sometimes, I just have to

07:51.514 --> 07:53.211
use our relationship
to push people.

07:53.255 --> 07:55.039
- Don't apologize.
You're in the home stretch.

07:55.083 --> 07:56.911
- Yeah, that building's
going to be a game-changer.

07:56.954 --> 07:59.304
- Hey.
- Hey.

07:59.348 --> 08:01.437
- [laughs]

08:01.481 --> 08:04.788
- Lena, how are you?
- Eh, doing okay.

08:04.832 --> 08:06.616
Just wish I could see
a little bit more

08:06.660 --> 08:08.749
of my husband these days.
- Ah-ha.

08:08.792 --> 08:12.753
- Uh, baby, baby, I know
I've been working long hours,

08:12.796 --> 08:16.974
but I promise you I'm going
to make it up to you, okay?

08:17.018 --> 08:18.976
- Well, just as long as we're
together tomorrow night.

08:19.020 --> 08:20.935
That's all I care about.

08:20.978 --> 08:24.068
- What's tomorrow night?
- Our anniversary?

08:25.679 --> 08:27.419
Okay.

08:27.463 --> 08:29.987
So help me, Terrence,
if you forget our anniversary,

08:30.031 --> 08:32.903
you will be sleeping
in that building of yours.

08:38.953 --> 08:41.738
- You think she bought it?
- I believe she did.

08:41.782 --> 08:43.871
- And Ali has everything set
tomorrow night at the bar?

08:43.914 --> 08:46.264
- It's all taken care of.
- Which reminds me,

08:46.308 --> 08:47.831
the jazz band we hired.
- Mm-hmm?

08:47.875 --> 08:49.746
- They can't do it.
So, you mentioned that

08:49.790 --> 08:52.096
that woman that fixed your sax
is tapped into that community.

08:52.140 --> 08:53.794
So do you think
you can make a call?

08:53.837 --> 08:55.360
See if she can get
someone else to do it?

08:55.404 --> 08:57.145
- Sure, I'll go down there
this afternoon.

08:57.188 --> 08:58.929
- And, uh--

08:58.973 --> 09:02.585
if you want to invite her
to the party, uh, I'm cool.

09:02.629 --> 09:05.066
- What?
- If you want to invite her--

09:05.109 --> 09:07.938
- I heard you the first time.
both: Yeah.

09:07.982 --> 09:10.550
- What's this?
- Your son dropped that off

09:10.593 --> 09:14.162
earlier to promote his podcast.
- I wasn't aware.

09:14.205 --> 09:15.859
- What?
- Nothing, it's--

09:15.903 --> 09:18.296
I mean, things have been good
between us lately.

09:18.340 --> 09:22.692
I thought maybe
we'd start sharing stuff.

09:22.736 --> 09:24.868
- Well, did you
ask him to, yet?

09:24.912 --> 09:26.827
[soft music]

09:26.870 --> 09:28.916
- I found out something
really interesting

09:28.959 --> 09:30.439
last night
about the God account.

09:30.482 --> 09:32.441
They changed the firewall.
- Whoa, what?

09:32.484 --> 09:34.095
- Yeah, completely
rewrote the code.

09:34.138 --> 09:35.792
- Wait, so what do you think
this means?

09:35.836 --> 09:37.664
- What if God unfriending you

09:37.707 --> 09:40.101
was about me getting too close
to cracking the firewall?

09:40.144 --> 09:41.711
- Okay, yeah, it's always
about you, Rakesh.

09:41.755 --> 09:43.931
- Oh, my God.
It's just a theory, Miles.

09:43.974 --> 09:46.194
Either way, I'm running
this new decryption program.

09:46.237 --> 09:47.978
I'll tell you what I find.
- All right.

09:48.022 --> 09:51.852
- So what's the deal
with, um, Hasan?

09:51.895 --> 09:53.636
You think you're supposed to
help him and his son?

09:53.680 --> 09:55.377
- It looks that way.
Look, the problem is

09:55.420 --> 09:58.467
Hasan is relying
on his faith to fix things

09:58.510 --> 10:01.731
instead of actually
doing something about it.

10:01.775 --> 10:04.168
I got to talk to Mateen.

10:04.212 --> 10:07.084
Cara's tracking down
his class schedule now.

10:07.128 --> 10:09.609
- Yeah, well, that's assuming
she's not busy texting Eli.

10:10.958 --> 10:13.961
Hey, you, uh--
you all right with that?

10:15.876 --> 10:18.269
- Yeah, yeah.

10:18.313 --> 10:21.229
The timing just wasn't right
for us, you know?

10:21.272 --> 10:22.796
[soft music]

10:22.839 --> 10:24.754
- You're experiencing regret,
though, right?

10:24.798 --> 10:26.669
I mean, it's in your eyes.

10:26.713 --> 10:28.671
- No, dude.

10:28.715 --> 10:31.587
Our poster!
Someone covered it up.

10:31.631 --> 10:33.589
[tense music]

10:33.633 --> 10:35.417
♪

10:35.460 --> 10:36.853
Who's DJ Trek?

10:36.897 --> 10:40.422
I spent $200
getting my posters made,

10:40.465 --> 10:43.730
and after one night,
they get hijacked by this guy?

10:43.773 --> 10:45.906
- DJ Trek.
Yeah, I've seen his posters

10:45.949 --> 10:48.125
all over town.
They're cool.

10:48.169 --> 10:49.910
If you're into
that sort of thing.

10:49.953 --> 10:52.521
- This isn't over.
I'm going to print

10:52.564 --> 10:54.175
a whole new batch of posters

10:54.218 --> 10:56.699
and plaster them over
every single one of these.

10:56.743 --> 10:59.049
- Don't you think you might be
taking this a bit personal?

10:59.093 --> 11:02.052
- My podcast
is on life support, okay?

11:02.096 --> 11:03.706
I need new listeners.

11:03.750 --> 11:05.708
These posters were supposed
to do that for me.

11:05.752 --> 11:07.405
So yeah,
I'm taking it personal.

11:07.449 --> 11:09.146
- Okay, moving on.

11:09.190 --> 11:11.148
Did you get the food
for Aunt Lena and Uncle T's

11:11.192 --> 11:12.933
party tomorrow night?
- Yes, yes, Sylvia's.

11:12.976 --> 11:14.456
Everything is taken care of.

11:14.499 --> 11:17.415
[tense music]

11:17.459 --> 11:21.289
Um, I'm sorry, Ali,
I have to run.

11:21.332 --> 11:22.943
- What, no wait,
we're supposed to have lunch

11:22.986 --> 11:25.032
and go over the appetizers.
- I know, I know.

11:25.075 --> 11:26.294
But something came up.

11:26.337 --> 11:28.775
- Let me guess,
the God account?

11:28.818 --> 11:31.734
- I'll see you tomorrow.
Talk to you later, Dee.

11:31.778 --> 11:35.259
♪

11:35.303 --> 11:37.914
- The God account?
You were serious about that?

11:40.961 --> 11:42.136
- Any idea what
you're going to say to him?

11:42.179 --> 11:43.615
- One of these times,

11:43.659 --> 11:45.313
I'll actually
have an answer for you.

11:45.356 --> 11:47.315
Look, there he is.

11:49.491 --> 11:51.014
- I can't keep
doing this anymore.

11:51.058 --> 11:52.581
- You know we don't
have a choice.

11:52.624 --> 11:55.540
- It looks like Hasan
was right about his son.

11:55.584 --> 11:57.238
He's definitely into
something shady.

11:57.281 --> 11:59.240
[tense music]

11:59.283 --> 12:00.894
♪

12:00.937 --> 12:03.287
- Yeah, let's find out what.

12:10.251 --> 12:13.428
[mischievous music]

12:13.471 --> 12:15.735
♪

12:15.778 --> 12:17.737
[keys jingle]

12:23.568 --> 12:25.788
- [clears throat]

12:25.832 --> 12:27.355
- Are you guys following me?

12:29.661 --> 12:32.142
- Actually, yes, we were.
- Yes.

12:32.186 --> 12:34.841
- We are.
- Uh...

12:34.884 --> 12:36.886
why?

12:36.930 --> 12:39.802
- We're friends
with Mateen's father.

12:39.846 --> 12:42.587
- Okay, I don't know what you
want, but you need to leave.

12:42.631 --> 12:44.067
- And we will once you tell us

12:44.111 --> 12:45.460
about the cell phone
Mateen gave you.

12:45.503 --> 12:47.375
What's going on?

12:47.418 --> 12:49.638
- David?

12:49.681 --> 12:52.554
- Tarah?
- What are you two doing here?

12:52.597 --> 12:56.950
- Uh, yeah, we could ask you
the same thing.

12:56.993 --> 12:58.821
Ooh, nice ring.

12:58.865 --> 13:00.736
- Please don't tell my father.

13:00.780 --> 13:02.085
He can't find out about us.

13:02.129 --> 13:03.783
- Why not?

13:05.654 --> 13:07.656
- Because David's Jewish.

13:07.699 --> 13:10.137
He'll never
allow this to happen,

13:10.180 --> 13:11.878
but it doesn't matter.

13:11.921 --> 13:13.227
We're getting married.

13:13.270 --> 13:15.577
[tense music]

13:15.620 --> 13:17.318
- Mazel tov?

13:24.020 --> 13:28.851
- So the cell phone Mateen
was hiding, it was yours?

13:28.895 --> 13:30.113
- Yes.

13:30.157 --> 13:32.159
He's been covering for us.

13:32.202 --> 13:33.638
But after everything
that happened

13:33.682 --> 13:35.423
at the house yesterday,

13:35.466 --> 13:37.294
he said he couldn't
be a part of this anymore.

13:37.338 --> 13:38.861
- Have you told your parents?

13:38.905 --> 13:41.255
- I told them about Tarah
right before I proposed.

13:41.298 --> 13:44.519
They lost it.
- Well, at least you asked.

13:44.562 --> 13:46.303
You don't even know
what your father would say.

13:46.347 --> 13:48.784
- Yes, I do.
My dad's a reasonable man,

13:48.828 --> 13:51.004
but not about his faith.

13:51.047 --> 13:53.702
Why do you care?
You just met my family.

13:53.745 --> 13:57.140
- Look, I know, but...

13:57.184 --> 13:58.881
after seeing
what happened yesterday

13:58.925 --> 14:01.666
between your father
and your brother...

14:01.710 --> 14:04.713
I happen to have experience
with that,

14:04.756 --> 14:07.629
and honestly, I was just seeing
if I could help.

14:07.672 --> 14:09.500
- We didn't mean to spy on you.

14:09.544 --> 14:11.198
We'll totally respect
your privacy.

14:11.241 --> 14:13.330
- But if there's anything
we can do for you,

14:13.374 --> 14:15.463
please, let us know.

14:15.506 --> 14:18.205
- Well, there is one thing.

14:18.248 --> 14:20.163
[tense music]

14:20.207 --> 14:23.906
- Mateen was supposed to be our
witness at the ceremony today.

14:23.950 --> 14:26.735
He's the only one
who knows about us.

14:26.778 --> 14:28.432
- Wait, whoa, wait, wait, wait.

14:28.476 --> 14:29.999
You two are getting married
today?

14:30.043 --> 14:31.740
- At the city clerk's office.

14:31.783 --> 14:34.003
Once we're married,
we're hoping our families

14:34.047 --> 14:37.877
will have no choice
but to try and accept this.

14:37.920 --> 14:40.183
You want to help?

14:40.227 --> 14:42.098
One of you can be our witness.

14:42.142 --> 14:44.796
- Oh, no, no,
I don't think we can do that.

14:44.840 --> 14:47.408
- Yeah, I can do that.

14:47.451 --> 14:48.931
[both gasp]

14:48.975 --> 14:51.107
- Really?
Thank you!

14:51.151 --> 14:53.153
- Uh-huh.

14:53.196 --> 14:55.024
- Miles, we can't do this
- Yeah she's right.

14:55.068 --> 14:56.721
I don't think
this is a good idea.

14:56.765 --> 14:59.899
- Guys, I'm helping two people
who are in love

14:59.942 --> 15:03.119
and want to be married
get married.

15:03.163 --> 15:04.816
- Yeah, behind
their parent's backs.

15:04.860 --> 15:07.210
How is that right?
- How is it right for a father

15:07.254 --> 15:08.951
to pick religion
over his child?

15:08.995 --> 15:10.953
- Okay, well,
Hasan hasn't made that choice.

15:10.997 --> 15:12.694
Tarah's made it for him.
- Yeah, not to mention,

15:12.737 --> 15:14.522
the God Account's not going
to be happy about this.

15:14.565 --> 15:16.741
Hasan's your friend suggestion,
not Tarah.

15:16.785 --> 15:17.917
There's no way
this is helping him.

15:17.960 --> 15:19.657
- If the God account thinks

15:19.701 --> 15:21.616
that I am going to stop Tarah
from getting married,

15:21.659 --> 15:22.965
then they chose the wrong guy.

15:23.009 --> 15:24.488
- Well, technically, Miles,

15:24.532 --> 15:26.186
you did the picking
this time, remember?

15:26.229 --> 15:28.971
- That doesn't mean that
I'm going to do its bidding.

15:29.015 --> 15:30.712
For this to work,

15:30.755 --> 15:33.758
I need to do things my way,
make my own decisions.

15:33.802 --> 15:36.370
Tarah and David
deserve to be happy.

15:36.413 --> 15:39.199
- Yeah, no, of course they do.

15:39.242 --> 15:40.678
But that's not
why you're doing this.

15:40.722 --> 15:42.115
- What are you talking about?

15:42.158 --> 15:44.117
- This is about
you and religion.

15:44.160 --> 15:45.901
That's why you're taking
such a hard line, Miles,

15:45.945 --> 15:47.947
and you know it.

15:47.990 --> 15:49.992
- Well, that doesn't mean
I'm wrong.

15:50.036 --> 15:51.907
- Okay, well, right or wrong,

15:51.951 --> 15:54.692
you're not the one who
has to live with the fallout.

15:54.736 --> 15:56.738
They do.

15:56.781 --> 15:58.479
I have to go meet
Liv and my mom.

15:58.522 --> 15:59.871
But I'll catch you guys later.

15:59.915 --> 16:02.613
[soft music]

16:02.657 --> 16:04.137
- [sighs]

16:04.180 --> 16:06.748
♪

16:06.791 --> 16:09.446
- This is a nice surprise.

16:09.490 --> 16:11.013
- It is?

16:11.057 --> 16:12.928
Um, uh,

16:12.972 --> 16:15.191
I mean...
thank you.

16:15.235 --> 16:16.671
[both laugh]

16:16.714 --> 16:18.238
How is your sax?

16:18.281 --> 16:22.155
- Oh, you did a--
a great job of fixing it.

16:24.287 --> 16:26.811
- Well, this is the part where
you tell me why you're here.

16:26.855 --> 16:28.770
[both laugh]

16:28.813 --> 16:30.815
- Right.
Um, I'm sorry.

16:30.859 --> 16:33.514
Uh, my brother-in-law
is throwing

16:33.557 --> 16:36.908
an anniversary party
for his wife tomorrow.

16:36.952 --> 16:39.650
- Oh, really?

16:39.694 --> 16:43.915
- And well, um, the band
cancelled at the last minute.

16:43.959 --> 16:45.569
- Oh, really?

16:45.613 --> 16:48.877
- I was hoping, maybe,
you would know a band

16:48.920 --> 16:52.054
that was up for
a last-minute gig?

16:52.098 --> 16:55.231
- Okay, I mean, I--
I could think of someone.

16:55.275 --> 16:57.494
Um...

16:57.538 --> 17:01.020
actually, there is
a great trio you can call.

17:02.630 --> 17:04.023
- Great, thanks.

17:04.066 --> 17:06.547
Um, this is a number
for the band?

17:06.590 --> 17:08.375
- That's mine.

17:09.854 --> 17:11.073
- Uh-huh.

17:11.117 --> 17:14.120
- You can call me
if they can't do it.

17:14.163 --> 17:16.774
- Right, okay.

17:16.818 --> 17:19.864
[both laugh]

17:19.908 --> 17:22.563
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

17:22.606 --> 17:25.566
♪

17:25.609 --> 17:28.482
- It's just a concert, Mom.

17:28.525 --> 17:30.701
Cara, tell her
it's just a concert.

17:30.745 --> 17:34.575
- Uh, yeah, you know,
Taylor Swift is pretty cool.

17:34.618 --> 17:36.620
- Just think about it.

17:36.664 --> 17:39.101
I know you'll make
the right decision.

17:45.368 --> 17:47.718
- Everything okay?

17:47.762 --> 17:51.331
- Yeah, I just--I had
a disagreement with Miles.

17:51.374 --> 17:52.854
- Anything you
want to talk about?

17:54.943 --> 17:57.554
- You know, I could use
your advice about Eli.

17:57.598 --> 17:59.121
He asked me out again.

17:59.165 --> 18:01.210
- And I assume you wouldn't
be asking for advice

18:01.254 --> 18:03.082
if you'd said yes.
- Right.

18:06.259 --> 18:08.478
Things with Eli and me,
they didn't really end well.

18:08.522 --> 18:11.481
- And you want to be careful.
- Yeah, but I don't know.

18:11.525 --> 18:13.222
I mean, he has changed.

18:13.266 --> 18:16.704
He quit his finance job,
and he seems really happy.

18:16.747 --> 18:19.141
He's kind of like a whole
new person, which is great.

18:19.185 --> 18:20.795
- So what's the problem?

18:20.838 --> 18:22.405
- That's the thing,
I don't know.

18:22.449 --> 18:25.713
I like Eli.
So why am I hesitating?

18:25.756 --> 18:27.454
What am I afraid of?

18:29.499 --> 18:30.979
- Can I ask you something?

18:31.022 --> 18:33.416
[soft music]

18:33.460 --> 18:36.376
If you knew things
would work out with Eli,

18:36.419 --> 18:38.943
would you still be hesitating?

18:38.987 --> 18:43.078
♪

18:43.122 --> 18:45.863
- I don't know, maybe.

18:45.907 --> 18:49.606
- So maybe this isn't
about Eli at all?

18:49.650 --> 18:51.608
Maybe it's about someone else?

18:56.135 --> 18:58.224
- Sorry, sorry I'm late.

18:58.267 --> 18:59.790
- We were beginning to think
you'd changed your mind.

18:59.834 --> 19:01.488
- No, just my shirt.

19:01.531 --> 19:04.055
I wanted to make sure
I was a witness with style.

19:04.099 --> 19:06.275
- So...

19:06.319 --> 19:09.322
want to get married?
- I do.

19:09.365 --> 19:11.193
- Come on.

19:13.717 --> 19:16.894
You two look great.
- Tarah.

19:16.938 --> 19:19.897
[tense music]

19:19.941 --> 19:22.291
- You told him.
How could you?

19:22.335 --> 19:25.164
- I'm sorry.
He has a right to know.

19:25.207 --> 19:28.776
- What are you doing here?
- He's going to be our witness.

19:28.819 --> 19:30.734
- You were going to marry him
without telling us?

19:30.778 --> 19:32.301
- I knew you
wouldn't understand.

19:32.345 --> 19:33.868
- And that makes it okay?

19:33.911 --> 19:36.436
- I know it may be hard
to accept, Hasan,

19:36.479 --> 19:38.089
but it is their decision.

19:38.133 --> 19:40.353
- Stay out of this.
This is not your family.

19:40.396 --> 19:42.224
♪

19:42.268 --> 19:44.052
Let's go.

19:44.095 --> 19:45.488
- Dad.

19:47.011 --> 19:49.144
We love each other.

19:49.188 --> 19:52.452
- That doesn't matter, Tarah.
You know that.

19:52.495 --> 19:54.889
- Hasan, please.
- He's not Muslim.

19:54.932 --> 19:57.196
- No, I'm not.
- Are you going to convert?

19:57.239 --> 20:00.938
- No, and I'm not asking Tarah
to convert, either.

20:02.592 --> 20:05.116
- If you marry this guy,

20:05.160 --> 20:07.249
you're no longer welcome
into our home.

20:07.293 --> 20:09.338
You're not my daughter anymore.
- Hasan.

20:09.382 --> 20:11.340
- [gasps]

20:11.384 --> 20:13.864
[somber music]

20:13.908 --> 20:16.476
- ♪ I don't agree

20:16.519 --> 20:18.521
♪

20:18.565 --> 20:22.351
♪ Every wound leaves a scar

20:22.395 --> 20:27.095
♪ They're all over me

20:27.138 --> 20:28.966
♪ They remind us
where we've been ♪

20:29.010 --> 20:30.620
- I'm sorry, David.

20:33.188 --> 20:34.581
- Go.

20:36.409 --> 20:38.889
You stay away from my family.

20:38.933 --> 20:40.717
Both of you.

20:40.761 --> 20:45.287
- ♪ It's to let them know

20:45.331 --> 20:46.810
♪

20:46.854 --> 20:51.162
♪ I know it's hard

20:51.206 --> 20:52.860
♪ It's time to carry on

20:57.995 --> 21:01.303
[knocking]

21:01.347 --> 21:04.263
- Dad, what are you doing here?
- I was on my home

21:04.306 --> 21:06.134
you know, to get ready
for the anniversary party.

21:06.177 --> 21:08.702
[stammers]

21:08.745 --> 21:11.182
I thought I'd stop by.
- Come on in.

21:11.226 --> 21:13.489
[upbeat music]

21:13.533 --> 21:16.971
- Oh, you know,
but if you're busy--

21:17.014 --> 21:18.538
- No, no, what's up?

21:18.581 --> 21:20.322
- Um...

21:20.366 --> 21:23.020
how's it all going?

21:23.064 --> 21:24.805
- Are you asking me
about my podcast?

21:24.848 --> 21:26.415
- Yes.

21:27.808 --> 21:29.505
- I'm still trying
to figure it out,

21:29.549 --> 21:31.681
but I appreciate you asking.

21:31.725 --> 21:33.422
- [chuckles]
Okay.

21:33.466 --> 21:35.859
- You know, Dad, I'm actually
glad you stopped by.

21:35.903 --> 21:37.818
There's something I could
use your advice on.

21:37.861 --> 21:39.167
- Really?
- Yeah.

21:39.210 --> 21:41.038
- Fire away.

21:41.082 --> 21:44.259
- Um...

21:44.303 --> 21:47.218
I have a friend

21:47.262 --> 21:49.351
from a devout
Islamic family.

21:49.395 --> 21:51.788
- Ah, beautiful faith, Islam.

21:51.832 --> 21:53.442
- She fell in love
with a Jewish guy.

21:53.486 --> 21:54.878
- Uh-huh.
- They were going

21:54.922 --> 21:56.880
to get married,
when her father found out.

21:56.924 --> 22:00.797
He stopped it,
forbid her from seeing him.

22:00.841 --> 22:02.973
- I see.

22:03.017 --> 22:06.281
- How does a father
choose religion

22:06.325 --> 22:07.935
over his own child?

22:07.978 --> 22:10.894
[tense music]

22:10.938 --> 22:14.550
- You really think that faith
and fatherhood is...

22:14.594 --> 22:15.769
that simple?

22:15.812 --> 22:17.988
♪

22:18.032 --> 22:21.557
- I think if her father
could separate the two,

22:21.601 --> 22:23.342
he would have made
a different choice.

22:23.385 --> 22:25.387
- Maybe he's thinking
about his daughter's happiness

22:25.431 --> 22:27.433
in the way that you can't.

22:27.476 --> 22:30.871
Your Uncle T and Aunt Lena
almost didn't get married

22:30.914 --> 22:33.439
because he was Episcopalian,
and her family was Catholic.

22:33.482 --> 22:35.223
- Oh, I didn't know that.
- Before I got a chance

22:35.266 --> 22:37.312
to speak with her father,

22:37.356 --> 22:39.880
they were planning
to hop a train to elope.

22:39.923 --> 22:44.841
- What did you say?
- At first, I just listened.

22:44.885 --> 22:46.930
Because I wanted to understand.

22:46.974 --> 22:49.890
And when I did,
I realized that her father

22:49.933 --> 22:53.372
was simply afraid
of losing his only daughter,

22:53.415 --> 22:56.331
and not just to an Episcopalian

22:56.375 --> 22:58.638
with a dashing smile.

22:58.681 --> 23:00.335
- [chuckles]

23:00.379 --> 23:04.078
- Most of the time,
our fears are more universal

23:04.121 --> 23:07.037
than we would like to admit,

23:07.081 --> 23:08.691
which is why we feel compelled

23:08.735 --> 23:12.086
to wrap them up
in things like...

23:12.129 --> 23:13.566
religion.

23:15.437 --> 23:16.482
- Thanks, dad.

23:18.005 --> 23:19.441
[bright music]

23:19.485 --> 23:21.443
- Hey, Miles, I need you
to come meet me at work.

23:21.487 --> 23:23.750
- I can't, I have my aunt
and uncle's anniversary party.

23:23.793 --> 23:26.361
- No, Miles, I found a crack
in the God account's firewall.

23:26.405 --> 23:28.145
My decryption program
is about to breach,

23:28.189 --> 23:30.278
but I need to tether it
to the IdentitySeal mainframe

23:30.321 --> 23:32.672
to boost my processing speed.
It's a two-person job, man.

23:32.715 --> 23:34.587
If this works, it could
tell us who's behind this.

23:34.630 --> 23:37.764
- Okay, look, I'm sorry.
Call Cara, see if she can help.

23:37.807 --> 23:39.461
There's something I need to do
before the party.

23:39.505 --> 23:41.202
- [scoffs]

23:41.245 --> 23:43.596
[phone beeps]

23:43.639 --> 23:45.032
- All right.

23:45.075 --> 23:46.555
[soft music]

23:46.599 --> 23:49.558
[man singing
in native language]

23:49.602 --> 23:56.609
♪

24:05.182 --> 24:08.621
- What are you doing here?
- I spoke to your wife,

24:08.664 --> 24:12.146
and she said you would be here.

24:12.189 --> 24:14.714
Look, I just want
to understand this.

24:14.757 --> 24:16.498
- No, you don't.

24:16.542 --> 24:18.239
You are here to judge.

24:18.282 --> 24:21.372
- Look, I didn't come all
the way down here to judge you.

24:21.416 --> 24:23.505
I'm supposed to be
with my family right now.

24:23.549 --> 24:25.507
My aunt and my uncle
are celebrating

24:25.551 --> 24:27.553
their 25th anniversary.

24:27.596 --> 24:29.642
Right now, my whole family

24:29.685 --> 24:32.688
is at my sister's bar,
waiting for me, but I'm here.

24:32.732 --> 24:35.125
I know how much your faith
means to you.

24:35.169 --> 24:38.520
- You think this
is about my faith?

24:38.564 --> 24:41.305
That I'm blindly following
some edict in the Quran?

24:41.349 --> 24:43.003
[tense music]

24:43.046 --> 24:46.180
This is about me
being her father.

24:46.223 --> 24:50.358
If Tarah wanted to drop out
of the law school,

24:50.401 --> 24:52.316
and I said no,

24:52.360 --> 24:55.711
would your opinion
be still so self-righteous?

24:55.755 --> 24:59.149
- But this is different.
- To you, maybe.

24:59.193 --> 25:02.718
To me, I see a mistake.

25:02.762 --> 25:06.983
A life of struggle,
separated from her family.

25:07.027 --> 25:10.291
Why would I want that
for my daughter?

25:10.334 --> 25:14.034
Why would I not try
to protect her from that?

25:14.077 --> 25:16.863
- Because she is in love.

25:16.906 --> 25:19.082
- Yes, she is.

25:19.126 --> 25:22.346
But she is an amazing woman,
and she will find love again.

25:22.390 --> 25:26.307
This time, with a man
who shares the same beliefs.

25:26.350 --> 25:30.746
Who raises the children
with the same beliefs,

25:30.790 --> 25:32.661
so they can be
part of our family.

25:32.705 --> 25:35.882
Part of our community.
- Look.

25:35.925 --> 25:40.713
I think you're scared
of losing her,

25:40.756 --> 25:43.977
and there is only one way
that's going to happen, Hasan.

25:44.020 --> 25:47.371
But David has nothing
to do with it.

25:49.635 --> 25:51.462
- Thank you, Miles.

25:53.421 --> 25:55.641
I think it's time
for you to go.

25:55.684 --> 25:58.644
[soft music]

25:58.687 --> 26:05.694
♪

26:10.699 --> 26:12.919
- About time!

26:12.962 --> 26:14.834
Uncle T and Aunt Lena
will be here any minute.

26:14.877 --> 26:16.792
- I hope they didn't see you.
- Yes, I'm sorry.

26:16.836 --> 26:18.141
I'm sorry, hello.

26:18.185 --> 26:20.927
I had to take care
of something.

26:20.970 --> 26:23.407
Oh, you got the band, Dad.

26:23.451 --> 26:25.888
- Yeah, Dad's friend, Trish,
really came through.

26:25.932 --> 26:29.631
- Oh, the Trish from Music Inn.
- Yes, why?

26:29.675 --> 26:31.502
- Nothing, she's really nice.

26:31.546 --> 26:33.853
[laughter]

26:33.896 --> 26:36.203
all: Surprise!
- Oh, my God!

26:36.246 --> 26:37.378
[laughter and applause]

26:37.421 --> 26:38.901
[camera snaps]

26:42.296 --> 26:44.080
[all aw]

26:44.124 --> 26:45.865
[tapping on glass]

26:48.694 --> 26:51.044
All right, so--
- Thank you.

26:51.087 --> 26:53.960
- I just want to thank everyone
for coming out

26:54.003 --> 26:56.919
and helping celebrate
my aunt and uncle

26:56.963 --> 26:58.878
on their 25th anniversary.

26:58.921 --> 27:01.576
[all cheer]

27:01.620 --> 27:03.273
More and more each day,

27:03.317 --> 27:08.061
I realize how much family
is important to me.

27:08.104 --> 27:10.498
You two are reminders

27:10.541 --> 27:13.936
of what love and commitment
is all about.

27:15.329 --> 27:19.463
Uncle T, you're like
a second father to me.

27:19.507 --> 27:21.901
You've always been
in my corner,

27:21.944 --> 27:23.511
and I love you.

27:23.554 --> 27:26.819
- I love you.
- To Aunt Lena and Uncle T.

27:26.862 --> 27:29.256
[cheering]

27:29.299 --> 27:30.953
[bright jazz music]

27:30.997 --> 27:33.695
[tense music]

27:33.739 --> 27:34.957
- Hey, thanks for doing this.

27:35.001 --> 27:36.655
I can't believe
Miles ditched me.

27:36.698 --> 27:38.091
- Yeah, no offense taken,
by the way.

27:38.134 --> 27:39.483
Hey, can I get a quick tour?

27:39.527 --> 27:40.571
- Uh, that's my desk
over there.

27:40.615 --> 27:41.921
Miles is right behind me.

27:41.964 --> 27:43.313
- [scoffs]

27:43.357 --> 27:46.099
♪

27:46.142 --> 27:48.536
You're an excellent tour guide.
- Sorry.

27:48.579 --> 27:51.060
IT's on break, and we don't
really have a big window.

27:51.104 --> 27:53.062
♪

27:53.106 --> 27:55.021
- Are you sure it's okay
to be doing this?

27:55.064 --> 27:56.675
- Uh, yeah.

27:56.718 --> 27:59.808
I'm just rerouting
the access point to my desk.

27:59.852 --> 28:03.812
All I need you to do
is go to my monitor

28:03.856 --> 28:06.946
and hit "session configuration"
when I tell you to.

28:06.989 --> 28:08.512
- Okay, seems easy enough.

28:08.556 --> 28:10.427
- Uh, yeah,
there's a small chance

28:10.471 --> 28:12.603
we might trigger
a system-wide security reboot,

28:12.647 --> 28:14.214
in which case,
we're going to have to exit

28:14.257 --> 28:16.216
through the side doors.
There are no cameras.

28:16.259 --> 28:17.739
- Excuse me, what?

28:17.783 --> 28:19.393
- Cara, we're this close
to breaking through

28:19.436 --> 28:21.308
the God account's firewall.

28:21.351 --> 28:22.962
We need to do this.

28:24.528 --> 28:28.228
[bright jazz music]
- [snapping]

28:28.271 --> 28:29.664
[chuckles]

28:29.708 --> 28:32.232
This band is all right.
- [laughs]

28:32.275 --> 28:33.624
- Please thank your friend
for me.

28:33.668 --> 28:35.409
- I will.

28:35.452 --> 28:37.890
- Speaking of which,
how'd it go?

28:39.587 --> 28:42.372
- Just fine, thank you.
- [laughs]

28:42.416 --> 28:43.939
[both laugh]

28:43.983 --> 28:47.247
- You know, it's not like
I haven't dated before.

28:47.290 --> 28:49.292
- When's the last time
you actually

28:49.336 --> 28:51.860
asked a woman out on a date?

28:51.904 --> 28:54.558
- Your sister,
and that went very well.

28:54.602 --> 28:56.038
- [inhales]

28:56.082 --> 28:57.953
I know how much
you loved my sister.

28:57.997 --> 28:59.128
We all did.

28:59.172 --> 29:01.522
But there is a difference

29:01.565 --> 29:04.699
between letting go,

29:04.743 --> 29:06.745
and moving on.

29:15.101 --> 29:18.539
- Come on, come on.
Almost there.

29:18.582 --> 29:19.670
[computer beeping]

29:19.714 --> 29:21.194
We're in.

29:21.237 --> 29:23.544
[computer beeping rapidly]

29:23.587 --> 29:25.328
Yes, it's working.

29:25.372 --> 29:28.201
[tense music]

29:28.244 --> 29:29.680
♪

29:29.724 --> 29:31.813
- What is that?
- Uh, it's definitely not

29:31.857 --> 29:34.163
a server address.

29:34.207 --> 29:35.861
It could be
the latitude and longitude,

29:35.904 --> 29:38.820
but not with a letter.

29:38.864 --> 29:41.170
- NO dot MTR.

29:42.824 --> 29:46.785
North?
North MTR?

29:46.828 --> 29:50.397
North Metro?
Could it be a train schedule?

29:50.440 --> 29:51.877
Look, 9:02,
that could be the time,

29:51.920 --> 29:54.662
and then, 35A could be
the track number.

29:56.882 --> 29:58.448
- You're right.

29:58.492 --> 30:01.887
It's for a train
leaving Grand Central today.

30:01.930 --> 30:05.064
Dude, you are way better
at this than Miles.

30:05.107 --> 30:06.674
- Thank you.

30:06.717 --> 30:08.458
[cell phone buzzing]
- Oh, excuse me.

30:08.502 --> 30:11.200
I have to take this
real quick.

30:13.681 --> 30:16.379
Hey, Rakesh, what's up?
- Miles, we did it.

30:16.423 --> 30:18.294
Cara and I hacked
the God account, bro.

30:18.338 --> 30:21.080
They're on the run, literally.
- What are you talking about?

30:21.123 --> 30:23.125
- Well, when we breached
the firewall,

30:23.169 --> 30:24.823
they gave us this info
about this train

30:24.866 --> 30:26.389
leaving Grand Central
in an hour.

30:26.433 --> 30:28.870
- Yeah, can you meet us there?
- Train schedule?

30:28.914 --> 30:30.524
That doesn't make any sense.

30:30.567 --> 30:31.917
- Well, unless the person
behind the God account

30:31.960 --> 30:33.353
is on that train.

30:33.396 --> 30:36.095
- Excuse me, sorry, sorry.

30:36.138 --> 30:39.663
- Okay, text me the info.
I'll meet you there.

30:41.491 --> 30:43.450
- Hey, what are you doing?
- I need to talk to you.

30:43.493 --> 30:46.105
I saw that you posted a picture
of this place on your Facebook.

30:46.148 --> 30:47.889
- Yeah, well, what's wrong?

30:47.933 --> 30:49.673
- Tarah is gone.

30:49.717 --> 30:51.632
Tell me, where is she?
- I don't know.

30:51.675 --> 30:53.895
- Don't lie to me,
you helped them the first time.

30:53.939 --> 30:55.897
- I'm not--
- Everything okay, Miles?

30:55.941 --> 30:58.465
- Yeah, yeah, yeah,
just give us a second.

30:58.508 --> 30:59.901
Yeah?

31:01.511 --> 31:04.819
Look, Hasan, I am telling you
the truth, okay?

31:04.863 --> 31:06.429
I didn't help them this time.

31:08.127 --> 31:09.780
What happened?

31:09.824 --> 31:11.782
- [heavy breathing]

31:11.826 --> 31:13.915
After we talked,

31:13.959 --> 31:15.438
I went home to talk to her

31:15.482 --> 31:17.136
to tell her
exactly what I told you.

31:17.179 --> 31:20.269
To make her understand, or at
least help me to understand.

31:20.313 --> 31:23.229
And when I got home,
she was gone.

31:23.272 --> 31:25.666
She packed most of her things,
and she left a note

31:25.709 --> 31:28.408
that she's leaving town
with David tonight.

31:28.451 --> 31:31.759
- Wait, leaving town tonight?
- Yes.

31:31.802 --> 31:33.282
- Grand Central Station!

31:33.326 --> 31:34.762
- What--what--
- And I know where they are.

31:34.805 --> 31:36.198
- Where, how?
- Just trust me.

31:36.242 --> 31:38.418
I'll explain on the way there.
Come on.

31:44.467 --> 31:45.729
- So you're telling me
the God account

31:45.773 --> 31:48.167
sent you my name
and a train schedule?

31:48.210 --> 31:50.125
- Look, I know how it sounds,
but it's true.

31:50.169 --> 31:52.171
Now, my friends are already
on their way down there.

31:52.214 --> 31:53.955
If they find Tarah and David,

31:53.999 --> 31:55.174
they're going to try
to talk to them,

31:55.217 --> 31:56.566
keep them from leaving.

31:56.610 --> 31:58.177
- Thank you for
doing this, Miles.

31:58.220 --> 32:01.528
I'm grateful that you are
helping me to stop them.

32:01.571 --> 32:03.095
- I'm not.

32:03.138 --> 32:05.227
You can't stop them, Hasan.

32:05.271 --> 32:06.837
Look, even if she was
to come home with you,

32:06.881 --> 32:08.883
what are you going to do?
Padlock her bedroom door?

32:08.927 --> 32:11.712
- Yes, if she hates me for the
rest of her life, so be it.

32:11.755 --> 32:13.409
- And you think that's going
to be the only thing

32:13.453 --> 32:15.237
she's going to wind up hating?

32:15.281 --> 32:17.022
- What do you mean?

32:17.065 --> 32:18.545
[soft music]

32:18.588 --> 32:20.373
- After my mother died,

32:20.416 --> 32:23.637
my father turned to his faith
to get him through it.

32:23.680 --> 32:26.031
He relied on God for answers,

32:26.074 --> 32:28.250
and without meaning to,

32:28.294 --> 32:29.469
he shut me out.

32:29.512 --> 32:31.688
♪

32:31.732 --> 32:34.387
A drunk driver took my mother
away from me,

32:34.430 --> 32:36.955
and religion took my father.

32:38.782 --> 32:41.263
If Tarah thinks that your faith

32:41.307 --> 32:44.397
is more important to you
than she is,

32:44.440 --> 32:47.400
how much longer do you think
before she gives up both?

32:47.443 --> 32:50.403
[soft dramatic music]

32:50.446 --> 32:53.275
♪

32:53.319 --> 32:55.756
[tense music]

32:55.799 --> 32:57.845
There they are.
Come on.

32:57.888 --> 32:59.847
Anything?
- Mm-mm.

32:59.890 --> 33:01.892
Couldn't find them.

33:01.936 --> 33:04.069
The train's already boarded.
- Yeah, it's leaving right now.

33:04.112 --> 33:06.985
- All right, let's go.
Let's go.

33:07.028 --> 33:13.992
♪

33:19.475 --> 33:22.000
- Tarah, Tarah!
Tarah, wait!

33:22.043 --> 33:25.046
Tarah, wait, wait,
wait, please.

33:25.090 --> 33:27.614
Stop, please!
Please open this door!

33:27.657 --> 33:29.964
Tarah!

33:30.008 --> 33:32.532
- Whatever you're going to say,
it won't make any difference.

33:32.575 --> 33:34.577
- Maybe not, but I have to try.

33:34.621 --> 33:36.884
[soft music]

33:36.927 --> 33:39.756
Please, you cannot do this.

33:39.800 --> 33:41.149
You cannot marry him like this.
- Good-bye, Dad.

33:41.193 --> 33:43.847
- Please let me finish.
Please?

33:45.458 --> 33:48.852
You cannot marry him
like this...

33:48.896 --> 33:52.639
because I must be there
when you sign the Kitab.

33:55.685 --> 33:57.296
I'm sure your parents,

33:57.339 --> 33:59.689
they want to be there
when you sign the Ketubah.

34:02.475 --> 34:05.608
Know from the born,

34:05.652 --> 34:08.002
I swore to protect you,

34:08.046 --> 34:10.483
and I won't let anything

34:10.526 --> 34:13.312
stand in the way
of your happiness.

34:15.618 --> 34:18.230
I just didn't imagine that,

34:18.273 --> 34:20.667
one day, that would be me.

34:22.799 --> 34:24.975
I'm so sorry.

34:26.499 --> 34:27.891
[speaking Dari]

34:31.504 --> 34:34.768
I love you.
I love you.

34:34.811 --> 34:37.597
[applause]

34:46.345 --> 34:49.130
- I can't believe the God
account played us again.

34:49.174 --> 34:51.698
- I'm sorry.
- You know what?

34:51.741 --> 34:54.657
It's time to bring out
the big guns.

34:54.701 --> 34:57.530
I'm going to reach out
to an old friend.

34:57.573 --> 35:00.010
- Okay.
- I'll talk to you guys later.

35:01.838 --> 35:03.275
- You're feeling
pretty good, huh?

35:03.318 --> 35:06.147
- Yeah, well, I went against
the God account,

35:06.191 --> 35:09.672
made my own choices,
and everything worked out.

35:09.716 --> 35:12.632
- Unless that's what it wanted
the whole time.

35:12.675 --> 35:14.721
- Look, and you were right.

35:14.764 --> 35:16.810
Hasan just needed
an opportunity

35:16.853 --> 35:17.985
to make his own choice.

35:18.028 --> 35:21.162
[cell phone buzzing]

35:21.206 --> 35:23.860
- And speaking of choices.

35:23.904 --> 35:25.688
It's Eli.

35:25.732 --> 35:28.996
- So, you going to give him
another shot?

35:29.039 --> 35:33.348
- I don't know.
I'm not sure what to do.

35:33.392 --> 35:35.263
- Look.

35:35.307 --> 35:38.136
Maybe Eli's the one.

35:38.179 --> 35:40.573
Maybe he's not.

35:40.616 --> 35:43.793
There's only one way
to find out.

35:43.837 --> 35:45.230
- And if he's not?

35:45.273 --> 35:47.754
[soft music]

35:47.797 --> 35:49.495
- Then you'll know.

35:49.538 --> 35:56.502
♪

35:56.545 --> 35:59.592
- I'd say this party
went off without a hitch.

35:59.635 --> 36:02.334
- I agree.

36:02.377 --> 36:04.031
You okay?

36:05.032 --> 36:06.686
- Why wouldn't I be?

36:06.729 --> 36:09.254
- Miles' speech about Terrence
being his second father.

36:09.297 --> 36:11.908
- Ah, well, he loves his uncle.

36:11.952 --> 36:13.954
I'd be lying
if I said I didn't--

36:13.997 --> 36:15.390
[clears throat]

36:15.434 --> 36:18.001
Envy it every once in a while.

36:18.045 --> 36:21.222
- Oh, I'm sorry.
Hey.

36:21.266 --> 36:23.703
I had to step out.
- Mm-hmm.

36:23.746 --> 36:26.532
You were gone?
- Ha, ha, ha, hilarious.

36:26.575 --> 36:27.968
Hey, Dad,
you remember the friend

36:28.011 --> 36:29.578
I was talking to you about?
- Yeah.

36:29.622 --> 36:31.711
- Guess what, she's getting
married after all.

36:31.754 --> 36:34.322
Her father came around.
- That's great, that's great.

36:34.366 --> 36:36.019
I assume you had something
to do with it.

36:36.063 --> 36:38.239
- I did, but also,
the help of some good advice.

36:38.283 --> 36:41.242
- [laughs]

36:41.286 --> 36:43.288
- What were you two
talking about?

36:43.331 --> 36:47.857
- Cake.
We were talking about cake.

36:47.901 --> 36:50.208
- Hey!
- I think I'm going to try

36:50.251 --> 36:51.644
and find your aunt and uncle.
- Yeah.

36:51.687 --> 36:53.385
- I thought you were
enjoying yourself.

36:53.428 --> 36:56.562
- I was just putting on
a good face for our family.

36:56.605 --> 36:58.999
- Do you trust me?

36:59.042 --> 37:01.697
Everything's going
to be fine, Lena.

37:01.741 --> 37:03.177
- How can you say that?

37:03.221 --> 37:04.787
- Because I have it
under control.

37:04.831 --> 37:05.962
- But you shouldn't
have kept it from me.

37:06.006 --> 37:08.269
- This is what I do!

37:08.313 --> 37:10.228
Lena--
- No, just--I'm going home.

37:10.271 --> 37:12.839
- Lena, Lena.
- Goodnight, Arthur.

37:12.882 --> 37:16.408
[tense music]

37:16.451 --> 37:17.974
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, yeah.

37:18.018 --> 37:20.455
She--she just wants
to go home early.

37:20.499 --> 37:24.285
You know, and I want
to enjoy myself, right?

37:24.329 --> 37:26.069
[laughs]

37:28.202 --> 37:31.553
Ah, nephew.
- Mm.

37:31.597 --> 37:34.077
- Man, that was
a beautiful speech.

37:34.121 --> 37:36.210
I love you for that.

37:36.254 --> 37:37.646
So I've been meaning
to ask you.

37:37.690 --> 37:39.866
How's it going
with those posters?

37:39.909 --> 37:42.477
- I can barely keep them up.

37:42.521 --> 37:45.611
This DJ plastered
all over them.

37:45.654 --> 37:48.483
- You're thinking
too small, man.

37:48.527 --> 37:51.051
Look, I got a good friend,
my first mentor.

37:51.094 --> 37:53.096
He's a brilliant man,
teaches marketing

37:53.140 --> 37:55.708
over at Harlem College.
You should take his class.

37:55.751 --> 37:58.101
And I can make a call,
if you want.

37:58.145 --> 38:00.408
- Yeah, yeah,
that'd be awesome.

38:00.452 --> 38:02.323
Thanks, Uncle T.
- You know.

38:02.367 --> 38:04.847
I do--do I not
do anything for you?

